1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,800
They're not coming in from another star system every other Tuesday.

2
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:04,300
They're present here.

3
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:10,180
There are handfuls of people doing weird things here and there.

4
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:12,000
Those people are all over the place.

5
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:15,780
Some of them I knew when I was at NASA have come to talk to me and said,

6
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:18,380
oh yeah, I was interested. I know something about this or that.

7
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:22,400
Have you met anybody working on the crafts themselves?

8
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:25,480
I've met people who've claimed to have worked on them or seen them.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:25,800
Really?

10
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,360
So yeah.

11
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:31,260
So the question I've had is why, when we had the NASA commission,

12
00:00:31,540 --> 00:00:35,360
why was there no section on what astronauts have seen in space?

13
00:00:37,260 --> 00:00:40,440
I talked to Alan Bean. He was from Apollo 12.

14
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:46,560
He said that when he went up to Skylab, they actually photographed a red flashing light.

15
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:51,720
Nobody puts lights on satellites. First, you don't need them. And second, it's more weight.

16
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:55,100
Also, satellites back then weren't doing proximity operations.

17
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:57,240
They were just following predictable orbits.

18
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:57,980
And they weren't changing orbits.

19
00:00:58,060 --> 00:00:59,040
They weren't changing orbits.

20
00:00:59,420 --> 00:00:59,680
Yeah.

21
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:04,080
They actually had a craft pull up alongside of them.

22
00:01:04,180 --> 00:01:04,540
Whoa.

23
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:05,320
Half their orbit.

24
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:08,640
And the cosmonaut drew a picture of the object.

25
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:13,220
The story in Musgrave, a shuttle pilot, also talked about seeing things like snakes.

26
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:14,140
Wow.

27
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,840
Things writhing around in space.

28
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:16,380
Really?

29
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,020
Yeah.

30
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:17,660
Yeah.

31
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:24,360
This is a phenomenon that people have seen for centuries.

32
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:26,560
This case is going back to the 1800s.

33
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,240
Back to Columbus.

34
00:01:27,380 --> 00:01:31,160
Balls of light coming out of the water, hovering next to the ship, following the ship, and then

35
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:32,200
taking off into the clouds.

36
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:37,140
And that's why I think there's probably bases underwater is your best bet.

